## FAQ: What Is an NDA Agreement

**What is an NDA agreement?**
An NDA (Non-Disclosure Agreement) is a legal contract preventing parties from sharing confidential information. It protects trade secrets, business strategies, and proprietary data.

**When should you use an NDA?**
Use an NDA whenever confidential information will be shared with third parties, including employees, investors, partners, or contractors who need temporary access to sensitive data.

**Is an NDA the same as a confidentiality agreement?**
Yes, NDA and confidentiality agreement are interchangeable terms. Both refer to legally binding contracts protecting confidential information from unauthorized disclosure.

